    "content": "# Welcome to Ballast - Building the Future of Link Management\n\nHey there! I'm Christer, the founder of Ballast. I wanted to take a moment to personally welcome you to our platform and share a bit about why we're building Ballast.\n\n## The Problem We're Solving\n\nAs someone who's been in the tech industry for years, I've always been frustrated by the complexity of existing link management tools. They're either too simple and lack the features you need, or they're overly complex with pricing that makes your head spin.\n\nI started Ballast because I believe link management should be:\n\n- **Simple** - Easy to use without a steep learning curve\n- **Powerful** - Rich analytics and insights when you need them  \n- **Affordable** - Fair pricing that scales with your needs\n- **Beautiful** - A tool you actually enjoy using\n\n## What Makes Ballast Different\n\n### AI-Powered Insights\n\nWe're not just another link shortener. Our AI analyzes your link performance and provides actionable insights to help you optimize your content strategy.\n\n### Developer-First Approach\n\nAs a developer myself, I know how important it is to have robust APIs and integrations. Ballast is built API-first, so you can integrate it into any workflow.\n\n### Focus on Privacy\n\nYour data is yours. We don't sell your information or track users across the web. Simple as that.\n\n## What's Next\n\nWe're just getting started! Over the coming months, you'll see us ship:\n\n- Enhanced analytics dashboard\n- Team collaboration features  \n- More integrations with your favorite tools\n- Mobile apps for iOS and Android\n\n## Join Us on This Journey\n\nBuilding a product is a journey, and I'd love for you to be part of it. Whether you're a casual user or managing links for a large organization, your feedback helps shape Ballast.\n\nFeel free to reach out to me directly on [Twitter](https://twitter.com/christerhagen) or [LinkedIn](https://linkedin.com/in/christerhagen). I read every message and love hearing from our users.\n\nThanks for being here, and welcome to Ballast!\n\n— Christer\n\n---\n\nReady to get started? Check out our [getting started guide](/blog/getting-started) or dive into our [advanced analytics features](/blog/advanced-analytics).",
